article.headline: Liberty 88, Coast Carolina 73
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Larry Blair scored 23 points and top-seeded Liberty cruised into the Big South tournament men's championship game with an 88-73 victory against fourth-seeded Coastal Carolina on Thursday night at the Vines Center. The Flames (16-14) will host High Point in the title game Saturday, with the winner earning an automatic NCAA tournament berth. High Point beat N.C.-Asheville 63-49. The Chanticleers (14-15) closed to within 71-68 on a 3-pointer by Kelvin Coggins with 2:44 to play, but faded after Brandon Newby left with an injury. Newby was 13-for-15 from the field with two 3-pointers and had 28 points in 30 minutes before leaving the game. Gabe Martin added 16 points and Louvon Sneed and Ryan Mantlo 10 each for Liberty. Moses Sonko and Colin Stevens scored 11 each for the Chanticleers, who were outrebounded 44-27 and outscored 22-11 from the free-throw line.
